1604124000.title: Managing Asia
1604124000.descr: Managing Asia is a series of in-depth conversations with some of the most influential business leaders in Asia today, who are changing the business landscape on the continent. Join host Christine Tan, as she interviews CEOs and entrepreneurs about various issues, as well as their professional inspirations and goals.

1604125800.title: Finding Solutions: Goalkeepers
1604125800.descr: CNBC's magazine explores issues considering racial equality, work diversity and inclusion all over the world. The programme brings the latest news stories dealing with these serious themes. It also includes experts' debates on these problems, as they try to come up with the best possible solutions for them.

1604127600.title: Air Travel In Turmoil
1604127600.descr: Join Shepard Smith as he examines the effect of the COVID-19 pandemic on U.S. airlines and on all the people who are working in the airline industry- pilots, flight attendants, gate agents, janitors, taxi drivers, and many others. Smith will talk to some of them about their daily challenges and all the changes they're facing, while he also investigates the future of airline industry.

1604131200.title: Answers With Bayless Conley (f)
1604131200.descr: In this religious television show Pastor Bayless Conley of the Cottonwood Christian Center, explains how religion can be used as a solution for various issues. Join him as he talks about the practical teachings of the Bible, while addressing serious problems, including depression and addiction.
